---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SubscribeBand from '../components/SubscribeBand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · David Henzel"
  description="David Henzel is a serial entrepreneur turning his portfolio into AI-native companies, and choosing love over fear. From Wiesbaden to LA to Bodrum, 25+ years building companies."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_380px] border-b border-ink">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-14 md:pt-16 pb-12 md:border-r border-ink">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-5">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif font-semibold text-[clamp(1.875rem,4.5vw,2.75rem)] leading-[1.15] mb-5">
        Recovering introvert. <span class="text-faint">Serial entrepreneur.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[15.5px] leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[520px]">
        Originally from Wiesbaden, Germany. Lived in Los Angeles for years. Now based in Bodrum,
        Türkiye. Turning companies AI-native, and living by
        <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="accent-link">Love Not Fear</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="relative min-h-[300px] md:min-h-[380px] border-t md:border-t-0 border-hairline">
      <img
        src="/images/david-headshot.png"
        alt="David Henzel"
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-top grayscale hover:grayscale-0 transition-[filter] duration-500"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 01 — The start -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">01 — The start</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 text-base leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[640px] space-y-4">
      <p>
        Hi, I'm David. I'm a systems thinker, a serial entrepreneur, and I'm obsessed with applying
        business principles to personal life.
      </p>
      <p>
        Growing up, I attended 14 different schools. Always the new kid. I was pretty lost and
        incredibly shy. I dropped out at 15, never got a degree, never had a real job. But I found
        entrepreneurship, and that gave me direction.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 02 — MaxCDN -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">02 — MaxCDN</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 text-base leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[640px] space-y-4">
      <p>
        In 2009, I moved from Germany to Los Angeles and co-founded <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MaxCDN" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">MaxCDN</a>.
        The business grew, but I was still deeply introverted. Making a phone call felt painful. So I
        forced myself through exposure therapy: Toastmasters twice a week, two networking events a
        week, talking to everyone even though it was incredibly uncomfortable. Over time, it worked.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then a yoga teacher said something that rewired everything: <em class="text-ink">"Every decision in life,
        you make out of love or out of fear."</em> I started seeing it everywhere. In sales, in
        leadership, in how I showed up at home. Most of what I thought were rational decisions were
        actually fear in disguise.
      </p>
      <p>
        Around the same time, my mother passed away from cancer and my wife was diagnosed with breast
        cancer. She's fine today. But it shook me. I did the <a href="https://community.lovenotfear.com/c/funeral-exercise" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">funeral exercise</a>,
        imagined myself on my deathbed, and asked: <em>did I live a good life?</em> The answer was
        clear. I wanted more impact. I wanted to find my real purpose.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 03 — The portfolio -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">03 — The portfolio</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 text-base leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[640px] space-y-4">
      <p>
        We had a successful exit with MaxCDN. I started applying the same frameworks I used in
        business — vision, mission, values, goals, habits — to my personal life, and it worked
        ridiculously well. I built a <a href="/companies" class="ink-link">portfolio of companies</a>,
        moved to Bodrum with my wife Yurda and our daughter Emma, and built
        <a href="https://dunyamvillage.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Dünyam Village</a>,
        a leadership retreat center. We live there with 10 dogs, horses, donkeys, chickens, and ducks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 04 — Today -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-ink">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">04 — Today</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 text-base leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[640px] space-y-4">
      <p>
        Today I'm doing the most exciting work of my life, with two centers of gravity: making my
        portfolio AI-native — and helping other companies do the same through
        <a href="https://relote.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Relote</a>, with the
        products we built along the way, <a href="https://contextengine.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Context Engine</a>
        and <a href="https://daimon.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Daimon</a> — and
        <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Love Not Fear</a>,
        the operating system for conscious leadership.
      </p>
      <p>
        Love Not Fear is still at the center of how I lead and hire. I help
        <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">students</a> find their path,
        <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/entrepreneurs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">entrepreneurs</a> find alignment, and
        <a href="https://lnfpeople.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">organizations</a> build culture rooted in purpose.
        I build all of it in public, and share what I learn as I go.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 05 — What I believe -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">05 — What I believe</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 text-base leading-relaxed text-body max-w-[640px] space-y-4">
      <p>
        Most personal development is backwards. People set goals, build habits, and grind, then wonder
        why they feel empty when they hit the number. That's because they skipped the foundation. You
        can't build a system for your life if you don't know what your life is for.
      </p>
      <p>
        Purpose comes first. Not passion. Purpose. Passion is what you enjoy. Purpose is what you'd do
        even when it's hard. Once you know that, values become your filter. Vision becomes your
        direction. Habits become your engine. In that order.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most fear-based decisions look rational on the surface. Staying in a job you've outgrown
        because "the market is tough." Not raising prices because "customers might leave." Not having
        the hard conversation because "the timing isn't right." These feel like logic. They're fear
        wearing a reasonable mask.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe the same thing about technology. AI transformation is real work, not a magic trick,
        and most of what gets sold is theater: prompting workshops, pilots that never touch a real
        workflow, advice from people who've never run a company. Done right, AI frees people to do
        their best work instead of replacing them. The company and the person are inseparable, so I
        build for both.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe you should build companies that make the world slightly less broken, not slightly
        more optimized. The best leaders are the ones who've done the inner work. You can be ambitious
        and kind at the same time, and anyone who tells you otherwise is protecting their own cynicism.
      </p>
      <p>
        Simplicity is a discipline, not a style. The hardest thing in business, and in life, is saying
        no to good things so you can say yes to the right things.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 06 — My values -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">06 — My values</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 max-w-[640px]">
      <ol class="space-y-5">
        {[
          ['First Things First', 'Always prioritize health and your loved ones. If it\'s not a "FUCK YES," it\'s a "NO."'],
          ['Own It', 'Always do your best. Be impeccable with your word. Do not complain or blame. Find solutions.'],
          ['Create Impact', 'Enrich the lives of everybody we come in touch with. Don\'t take things personal. Do not make assumptions.'],
          ['Unconditional Love', 'Make decisions out of love, not fear.'],
          ['Simplicity', 'Be authentic. Only do and buy things that matter.'],
        ].map(([title, body], i) => (
          <li>
            <p class="font-serif font-semibold text-lg text-ink mb-1">{i + 1}. {title}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-body leading-relaxed">{body}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-7 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
        Want to define your own? I built a free AI tool that walks you through it.
        <a href="https://community.lovenotfear.com/c/define-your-personal-core-values" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="ink-link">Discover your core values here</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 07 — Operating system -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] border-b border-hairline">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">07 — Operating system</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 max-w-[640px] space-y-8">
      <p class="text-base text-body leading-relaxed">
        I run my own life on the same operating system I bring to a company: vision, mission, values,
        goals, habits. Here's the top of mine.
      </p>
      <div>
        <p class="table-label mb-3">Professionally</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[22px] text-ink leading-[1.35]">
          A world where people and organizations thrive through better systems, technology, and
          choices rooted in love rather than fear.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base text-body leading-relaxed">
          Build companies, tools, and frameworks that help individuals and organizations grow, work
          better, and live more intentionally, by combining technology, practical methodology, and
          the practice of acting from love rather than fear.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="table-label mb-3">Personally</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[22px] text-ink leading-[1.35]">
          Live a long, healthy, impactful, happy, and fulfilled life. Stay mentally and physically
          fit, learning and growing until the end.
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="table-label mb-3">As a family</p>
        <blockquote class="font-serif font-semibold text-xl md:text-[22px] text-ink leading-[1.35]">
          Empower, protect, and lead the people you love.
        </blockquote>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base text-body leading-relaxed">
          Provide your family with everything they need to thrive physically, mentally, and
          emotionally. Remove uncertainty and provide direction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 08 — Who I help -->
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[220px_1fr]">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 pt-9 md:py-9 table-label md:border-r border-hairline">08 — Who I help</div>
    <div class="px-6 md:px-8 py-6 md:py-9 max-w-[640px]">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-6">
        <div class="border-t border-ink pt-4">
          <h3 class="font-serif font-semibold text-lg text-ink mb-2">Founders and leaders</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
            Running a real company? I help you rebuild it around AI, and build a culture where people
            do their best work out of love, not fear.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-ink pt-4">
          <h3 class="font-serif font-semibold text-lg text-ink mb-2">Individuals</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
            Building your own life? The Love Not Fear operating system helps you find your purpose,
            define your values, and build habits that actually stick.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-3">
        <a href="/cal" class="btn-pill">Book a call</a>
        <a href="/speaking" class="accent-link text-sm font-medium">Have me speak →</a>
        <a href="/companies" class="accent-link text-sm font-medium">See the ventures →</a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-mute">Much love.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SubscribeBand
    id="about"
    copy="Want to follow the journey? Occasional essays on building companies, finding purpose, and the Love Not Fear operating system."
  />
</BaseLayout>
